  bugScientificName: Papilio polyxenes
  bugFact: "Black Swallowtails are often confused with Pipevine Swallowtails and
    Spicebush Swallowtails. They mimic the appearance of Pipevine Swallowtails with
    the underside of their wings. This is used to confuse predators into making them
    think they\u2019re poisonous. "
